1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:53,990 --> 00:01:55,860
No!

3
00:01:55,860 --> 00:01:57,070
Listen, Nami.

4
00:01:57,070 --> 00:02:00,970
Using the Climate Baton in battle
starts with using your head!

5
00:02:00,970 --> 00:02:02,810
Keep your wits about you to survive!

6
00:02:03,170 --> 00:02:05,360
That's our true weapon after all.

7
00:02:07,520 --> 00:02:09,190
Heat balls and cool balls...

8
00:02:09,190 --> 00:02:12,040
Combining them makes
full use of their attributes!

9
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:13,530
That's the power of the Climate Baton!

10
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:27,380
And one last thing:

11
00:02:27,380 --> 00:02:31,400
Tornado Tempo!
It's this weapon's flagship move!

12
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:33,570
Tornado Tempo...

13
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:39,350
As long as your opponent is human,
they won't be standing after getting hit.

14
00:02:39,350 --> 00:02:42,160
But you only get one shot,
so use it as a last resort.

15
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:44,220
If you miss, consider it over.

16
00:02:44,220 --> 00:02:46,350
If I miss, it's over...

17
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:48,480
Pay attention.

18
00:02:52,440 --> 00:02:54,800
Interesting weapon you've got there...

19
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:59,990
But without effective attacks,
isn't it just a toy?

20
00:03:00,630 --> 00:03:06,000
Its original design doesn't matter.
It's a only a weapon... when...

21
00:03:14,050 --> 00:03:15,840
it harms someone.

22
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:18,380
If I don't hurry up, I'll be killed...

23
00:03:18,380 --> 00:03:22,100
The final, most powerful technique...
Tornado Tempo... I need to be quick!

24
00:03:25,190 --> 00:03:26,060
G-Give that back!

25
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:30,400
You can't kill me with a toy like this.

26
00:03:31,580 --> 00:03:34,530
A sweater could build up
a better charge than this.

27
00:03:34,920 --> 00:03:37,940
We won't know until I try!

28
00:03:37,940 --> 00:03:39,620
Give it back to me!

29
00:03:43,630 --> 00:03:45,080
Think!

30
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:50,330
If I lower her guard, she can't dodge
the one-shot attack, Tornado Tempo!

31
00:03:50,330 --> 00:03:51,040
It might work!

32
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:53,420
Three types of air bubbles...

33
00:03:53,420 --> 00:03:57,610
Is there some way to use them
in this country's parched climate?

34
00:03:57,610 --> 00:04:00,670
If only there was
a little more moisture in the air!

35
00:04:00,670 --> 00:04:04,520
Moisture... That's right! If I remember
correctly, there's a rain technique...

36
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:12,190
Rain Tempo!

37
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:13,900
Water tricks, huh?

38
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:16,740
Sprinkler!

39
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:18,200
You seem desperate.

40
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:21,210
No! I have a plan!

41
00:04:21,210 --> 00:04:23,910
Enough already. You can
stop with the parlor tricks.

42
00:04:27,210 --> 00:04:29,870
The party is at its height.
Let's call it quits.

43
00:04:30,330 --> 00:04:30,920
A sea urchin?!

44
00:04:31,650 --> 00:04:34,090
Sea Urchin Stinger!

45
00:04:39,570 --> 00:04:41,260
I'll poke you full of holes!

46
00:04:50,910 --> 00:04:53,770
So much for poking holes...
She incinerated the wall!

47
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:59,650
You put on a great show earlier,
so allow me to return the favor.

48
00:05:01,630 --> 00:05:02,400
Now's my chance!

49
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:03,490
Heat Ball!

50
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:15,200
Hot air rises while absorbing moisture.

51
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:19,800
It rapidly cools when it hits
descending cold air, freezing the moisture.

52
00:05:21,340 --> 00:05:22,400
That's when...

53
00:05:23,740 --> 00:05:26,510
Spike-Spike Doping!

54
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:31,560
I said pay attention, didn't I?!

55
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:33,560
Stinger Flail!

56
00:05:51,780 --> 00:05:56,350
My goodness. I suppose you're
at least an expert in running away.

57
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:00,760
Right! The air bubbles!

58
00:06:08,460 --> 00:06:09,510
It formed!

59
00:06:09,510 --> 00:06:11,760
It's small, but it's a cloud alright!

60
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:13,520
What the hell?

61
00:06:14,350 --> 00:06:17,440
Not enough. It needs to be bigger!

62
00:06:18,110 --> 00:06:19,650
Cool Ball!

63
00:06:20,230 --> 00:06:21,280
Heat Ball!

64
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:25,780
That's enough out of you!

65
00:06:27,790 --> 00:06:29,040
You wretched little...!

66
00:06:31,830 --> 00:06:34,000
Stinger Flail!

67
00:06:38,870 --> 00:06:41,130
So? Are you ready to die?

68
00:06:42,410 --> 00:06:43,760
Are you?

69
00:06:44,740 --> 00:06:46,400
Bluffing, I see.

70
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:55,850
Got you.

71
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:19,210
You'll pay for that!

72
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:27,890
What?!

73
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:29,720
For today's weather,

74
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:32,030
the wind and humidity are both stable,

75
00:07:32,030 --> 00:07:35,890
and we have a high pressure system
on this fine, sunny day.

76
00:07:36,260 --> 00:07:42,630
However, in one particular area,
you may find mirages and cyclones.

77
00:07:45,140 --> 00:07:47,710
Be on the lookout for tornadoes.

78
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:53,110
Tornado Tempo!
It's this weapon's flagship move!

79
00:07:53,110 --> 00:07:55,860
But you only get one shot,
so use it as a last resort.

80
00:07:55,860 --> 00:07:57,750
If you miss, consider it over.

81
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:01,040
If I miss, it's over...

82
00:08:02,220 --> 00:08:03,870
Beware of twisters!

83
00:08:07,650 --> 00:08:09,220
Are you okay?

84
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:15,650
Your left leg has taken
a lot of punishment.

85
00:08:16,890 --> 00:08:19,550
You won't be able to stand
for much longer.

86
00:08:23,610 --> 00:08:25,320
Sea Urchin Stinger!

87
00:08:39,270 --> 00:08:41,960
This is... nothing...!

88
00:08:43,130 --> 00:08:45,580
It doesn't hurt at all!

89
00:08:45,580 --> 00:08:48,110
Don't you know how much
she's suffered?!

90
00:08:49,650 --> 00:08:52,090
Compared to her pain...

91
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:58,980
a leg or two, or three...

92
00:08:59,650 --> 00:09:00,770
don't mean a thing!

93
00:09:03,850 --> 00:09:05,310
This is it!

94
00:09:05,900 --> 00:09:08,110
Tornado Tempo!

95
00:09:29,250 --> 00:09:30,220
Huh?

96
00:09:36,540 --> 00:09:39,180
Wha...? What?
Wh-What in the world?!

97
00:09:39,180 --> 00:09:41,190
The doves wrapped around me!

98
00:09:58,500 --> 00:09:59,640
Ow...

99
00:10:53,410 --> 00:10:57,510
I did it... I did it! Usopp... Vivi...!

100
00:11:10,810 --> 00:11:16,070
What is he talking about? Pluton?
What in the world is he...?

101
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:22,180
I hear that one shot from Pluton
can completely destroy an island.

102
00:11:29,170 --> 00:11:32,660
Named after a god, it was
antiquity's most devastating weapon.

103
00:11:32,660 --> 00:11:36,300
It should be hidden
somewhere in this country.

104
00:11:38,490 --> 00:11:42,070
An ancient weapon?
Such a thing exists here...

105
00:11:42,870 --> 00:11:44,270
and my father knew?

106
00:11:44,650 --> 00:11:47,440
A secret passed down
with the throne...

107
00:11:47,770 --> 00:11:50,980
That's been my target from the start.

108
00:11:50,980 --> 00:11:55,610
With it, I'll build a state with
the most fearsome military right here.

109
00:11:56,230 --> 00:11:59,200
That's been your aim all this time?!

110
00:12:00,490 --> 00:12:02,940
Once I become the king,

111
00:12:02,940 --> 00:12:07,460
I'll easily draw the local pirates
under my umbrella,

112
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:12,750
expanding my influence until
I can best the World Government.

113
00:12:12,750 --> 00:12:14,760
This will be a country of dreams!

114
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:18,580
Impossible! The World Government
will not stand for it!

115
00:12:18,580 --> 00:12:23,720
They probably won't, which is
precisely why I need Pluton.

116
00:12:24,100 --> 00:12:27,630
I don't know where you
could have heard that name,

117
00:12:27,630 --> 00:12:29,560
but I don't know its location.

118
00:12:30,160 --> 00:12:35,530
I cannot even verify if it truly
exists somewhere in this land.

119
00:12:35,900 --> 00:12:38,910
I see. What you say
probably isn't a complete lie...

120
00:12:40,370 --> 00:12:43,400
and I feared that might be the case.

121
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:49,500
Even I know that its
very existence remains in doubt.

122
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:59,300
What noisy flies...

123
00:13:00,340 --> 00:13:03,560
I heard that Crocodile
crucified King Cobra.

124
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:05,150
Save His Majesty!

125
00:13:05,150 --> 00:13:08,100
We have to find
a way inside at any cost!

126
00:13:08,470 --> 00:13:11,940
But those hands sprouting
from the door are keeping us out!

127
00:13:12,410 --> 00:13:14,950
We're stuck until we
do something about them!

128
00:13:16,760 --> 00:13:18,510
Just as I had planned,

129
00:13:18,510 --> 00:13:24,430
the Rebel Army will reach that square
in twenty minutes and start fighting.

130
00:13:25,910 --> 00:13:30,040
And then—that is to say,
30 minutes from now at 4:30—

131
00:13:32,980 --> 00:13:37,540
I've ordered a powerful blast
aimed at the square.

132
00:13:44,370 --> 00:13:45,800
Are you insane?!

133
00:13:46,510 --> 00:13:49,580
It's designed to level anything
within five kilometers.

134
00:13:49,580 --> 00:13:51,770
The view from here
will greatly change.

135
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:53,730
If you do that...!

136
00:13:54,810 --> 00:13:58,510
No one from either the Royal Army
or the Rebel Army will survive.

137
00:13:58,510 --> 00:14:01,740
Hence, the battle will
cease permanently.

138
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:08,830
Doesn't that please you? After all,
you wanted so badly to stop them.

139
00:14:10,040 --> 00:14:14,120
Instead of meticulously
trying to blow up the palace,

140
00:14:14,420 --> 00:14:19,170
you'll reach your goal quicker
by just blowing up both armies.

141
00:14:19,450 --> 00:14:22,220
How can you do such a thing?!

142
00:14:22,220 --> 00:14:25,590
What could they have done
to deserve this kind of fate?!

143
00:14:25,590 --> 00:14:28,030
You are... You are...

144
00:14:28,030 --> 00:14:28,510
Your Highness...!

145
00:14:28,950 --> 00:14:30,140
They're worthless.

146
00:14:31,130 --> 00:14:33,790
Please stop this!
What good will come of it?

147
00:14:33,790 --> 00:14:34,900
Princess Vivi!

148
00:14:34,900 --> 00:14:38,110
Now, Mr. Cobra. Let me
ask you another question.

149
00:14:42,290 --> 00:14:45,700
Where can I find the poneglyph?

150
00:14:45,970 --> 00:14:48,660
Poneglyph... Why would you need...?

151
00:14:50,520 --> 00:14:52,960
If I tell you where it is...

152
00:14:55,350 --> 00:14:59,710
No... I'll show you.

153
00:15:00,730 --> 00:15:01,670
Papa...

154
00:15:04,060 --> 00:15:07,390
That's the wise King Cobra
for you! You're a clever man.

155
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:09,850
Your Highness!

156
00:15:11,130 --> 00:15:14,800
I can't... take this any more!

157
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:44,110
I'll show you...
the difference in pride...

158
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:47,910
between your swords and mine!

159
00:15:47,910 --> 00:15:49,390
Three-Sword Style...

160
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:53,010
Bull...

161
00:15:53,010 --> 00:15:54,390
Spines!

162
00:15:56,210 --> 00:15:57,440
Spider...

163
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:21,430
So basically, your body
is hard as steel.

164
00:16:21,430 --> 00:16:24,380
If I can't cut steel,
then I can't cut you, huh?

165
00:16:24,970 --> 00:16:27,030
That would be correct.

166
00:16:27,570 --> 00:16:30,090
Smashing and cutting attacks
don't work on me.

167
00:16:32,420 --> 00:16:34,520
I admit, this one's a toughie.

168
00:16:34,520 --> 00:16:38,140
Since I'm not yet capable of
cutting steel, I can't defeat you now.

169
00:16:39,440 --> 00:16:41,230
Then what's your next move?

170
00:16:41,230 --> 00:16:43,650
Simple. I'll give you my sympathy.

171
00:16:43,650 --> 00:16:44,820
What?

172
00:16:46,680 --> 00:16:49,430
I've been looking forward
to an obstacle like this.

173
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:54,120
I was thinking that it's high time
I reached the next level.

174
00:16:55,390 --> 00:16:57,890
When I defeat you,

175
00:16:57,890 --> 00:17:01,590
I'll be a man who can even cut steel.

176
00:17:17,680 --> 00:17:21,140
When you defeat me, huh?

177
00:17:21,140 --> 00:17:23,710
You might want
to curb your enthusiasm.

178
00:17:24,440 --> 00:17:28,100
Just know that ever since
I gained my Dice-Dice powers,

179
00:17:28,100 --> 00:17:31,760
not a single so-called swordsman
has so much as scratched me.

180
00:17:32,650 --> 00:17:36,570
Those who wield swords...
are powerless before me.

181
00:17:36,570 --> 00:17:39,100
Yeah, I get the picture.

182
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:42,980
Then we can go ahead and close
the book on those tales of yours.

183
00:17:42,980 --> 00:17:46,920
I don't know how many swordsmen
you've fought in the past,

184
00:17:47,650 --> 00:17:50,630
but you and I are meeting
for the first time.

185
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:55,930
It seems that at least
your tongue is sharp.

186
00:17:57,470 --> 00:17:59,310
Thanks, baldy.

187
00:18:04,260 --> 00:18:06,020
We'll see how long you'll last.

188
00:18:06,470 --> 00:18:07,520
Right back at you.

189
00:18:50,630 --> 00:18:51,490
Oni...

190
00:18:53,530 --> 00:18:54,940
Giri!

191
00:18:59,450 --> 00:19:00,950
Tiger...

192
00:19:00,950 --> 00:19:01,700
Trap!

193
00:19:34,430 --> 00:19:36,030
I told you, didn't I?

194
00:19:39,740 --> 00:19:43,950
It's a little shocking that you
didn't even get a single bruise...

195
00:19:44,330 --> 00:19:49,680
And I've never seen an opponent
still standing after solid hits like that.

196
00:19:50,360 --> 00:19:51,960
Of course you haven't.

197
00:19:52,320 --> 00:19:56,130
After all, we're meeting
for the first time.

198
00:20:06,010 --> 00:20:07,390
That's right!

199
00:20:08,120 --> 00:20:10,700
This guy's a human blade.

200
00:20:10,700 --> 00:20:13,480
Every part of his body
is a cutting edge!

201
00:20:17,740 --> 00:20:19,870
Sparkling Daisy!

202
00:20:26,710 --> 00:20:29,420
H-He's...

203
00:20:30,190 --> 00:20:31,250
Begone.

204
00:21:01,290 --> 00:21:04,010
I train harder than anyone I know.

205
00:21:07,430 --> 00:21:11,970
I've had to face my limitations
in many difficult situations before.

206
00:21:14,080 --> 00:21:16,790
What is it that I lack?!

207
00:21:19,150 --> 00:21:22,110
Sensei...! Sensei!

208
00:21:23,050 --> 00:21:24,350
Hmm?

209
00:21:25,270 --> 00:21:28,890
There are men in this world who can
cut through anything? Even steel?

210
00:21:28,890 --> 00:21:29,810
Is that true?!

211
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:34,930
Yes, it's true.

212
00:21:36,580 --> 00:21:40,280
Now, watch this paper carefully, Zoro.

213
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:48,750
Sensei, you didn't cut it.

214
00:21:49,110 --> 00:21:50,660
Listen well, Zoro.

215
00:21:50,660 --> 00:21:56,380
There are swordsmen out there
who are capable of cutting nothing.

216
00:21:58,510 --> 00:22:04,720
But they can also cut anything,
even steel—using the very same blade.

217
00:22:05,850 --> 00:22:10,000
The height of swordsmanship is protecting
exactly what one wishes to protect

218
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:12,280
and cutting exactly
what one wishes to cut.

219
00:22:13,310 --> 00:22:15,980
A blade that injures
all that it touches...

220
00:22:15,980 --> 00:22:19,440
Well, to me, that isn't
true swordsmanship.

221
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:21,300
Do you understand?

222
00:22:32,830 --> 00:22:36,350
Sensei, I'll be a swordsman
who can cut anything!

223
00:22:37,300 --> 00:22:40,760
Zoro, did you hear a word I said?

224
00:22:51,140 --> 00:22:54,380
See if you can nick me already.

225
00:22:55,060 --> 00:22:58,600
You'll never scratch me
if you're always on the defensive.

226
00:22:59,770 --> 00:23:06,320
Unfortunately, you'll never get
to see me as I resolutely cut steel...

227
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:15,420
because when I do cut steel,
that's when you'll be dead.

228
00:23:17,040 --> 00:23:18,380
So you say.

229
00:23:27,250 --> 00:23:31,010
I'll cut anything
and everything... into pieces!

230
00:23:33,350 --> 00:23:37,800
"Swordsmen capable
of cutting nothing," huh?

231
00:23:40,770 --> 00:23:44,370
Cut nothing... but also cut steel.

232
00:23:44,370 --> 00:23:46,780
I don't understand
what it means at all!

233
00:23:47,950 --> 00:23:51,700
Keep thrusting onward! That's
the secret to a more powerful sword!

234
00:23:52,280 --> 00:23:54,350
Atomic Spar!

235
00:23:56,810 --> 00:23:58,580
I'll just cut you up!

236
00:24:27,110 --> 00:24:29,740
Crab... Grab!

237
00:24:51,190 --> 00:24:53,300
I've about had it with this guy.

238
00:24:54,790 --> 00:24:56,310
The feeling is mutual.

239
00:24:57,250 --> 00:25:00,900
Let me tell you one thing.
Do not consider me a swordsman.

240
00:25:02,020 --> 00:25:06,310
I am full of weapons
that can dice you into pieces.

241
00:25:12,250 --> 00:25:13,490
Spiral Hollow!

242
00:25:18,410 --> 00:25:20,870
Not a swordsman...
So then you're an excavator?!

243
00:25:21,860 --> 00:25:23,330
I'm an assassin!

244
00:25:26,840 --> 00:25:30,340
Sparks?! Just how fast
is he spinning?!

245
00:25:32,970 --> 00:25:33,930
I can't hold it...!

246
00:25:36,470 --> 00:25:41,730
I could never be an excavator.
I'd pulverize anything I touch.

247
00:25:43,160 --> 00:25:43,940
Crap!

248
00:25:59,490 --> 00:26:02,320
A moment's miscalculation invites...

249
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:04,580
death!

250
00:26:26,580 --> 00:26:28,370
You're still breathing...

251
00:26:33,750 --> 00:26:36,390
I can't turn my back to him...!

252
00:26:38,610 --> 00:26:41,000
Why keep struggling
when you're disarmed?

253
00:26:44,810 --> 00:26:47,210
Spar Break!

254
00:27:05,200 --> 00:27:06,940
Rest in peace.

255
00:27:09,970 --> 00:27:11,520
Today...

256
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:14,620
is not my day for stone.

257
00:27:33,040 --> 00:27:36,470
The others... I wonder if they're okay.

258
00:27:52,370 --> 00:27:56,430
How are you still standing?
I sliced you to shreds.

259
00:27:56,970 --> 00:27:59,470
Did you dodge
all of those falling stones?

260
00:28:05,630 --> 00:28:08,720
These stones... Did I dodge them?

261
00:28:09,230 --> 00:28:10,630
No...

262
00:28:11,150 --> 00:28:15,630
I knew... where the stones would land.

263
00:28:20,480 --> 00:28:22,060
One of my swords...

264
00:28:22,550 --> 00:28:24,420
is there, under that stone.

265
00:28:25,350 --> 00:28:26,400
I can tell.

266
00:28:30,040 --> 00:28:31,230
What's he doing...?

267
00:28:40,490 --> 00:28:43,060
I've experienced this feeling before.

268
00:28:47,210 --> 00:28:49,120
Everything goes silent around me.

269
00:28:50,850 --> 00:28:54,130
I become keenly aware
of my own heartbeat.

270
00:28:57,150 --> 00:29:00,640
It's as if... I'm standing close
to the gates of hell.

271
00:29:03,570 --> 00:29:09,520
When the stones were falling,
I could sense them as if they were alive.

272
00:29:11,210 --> 00:29:14,670
No, I didn't sense them...
It was more distinct than that.

273
00:29:15,520 --> 00:29:16,720
Rhythm...

274
00:29:18,350 --> 00:29:20,700
A stone's... rhythm.

275
00:29:21,640 --> 00:29:23,680
Trees have their own rhythm.

276
00:29:24,810 --> 00:29:29,160
Even the soil has its own.
Is that what this is?

277
00:29:30,550 --> 00:29:31,830
Listen well.

278
00:29:31,830 --> 00:29:36,930
There are swordsmen out there
who are capable of cutting nothing.

279
00:29:39,200 --> 00:29:41,000
When cutting nothing...

280
00:29:41,920 --> 00:29:44,510
Is that knowing the rhythm?

281
00:29:45,640 --> 00:29:49,640
Is this... the power to cut even steel?

282
00:29:51,110 --> 00:29:54,550
You... How did you manage this?

283
00:29:54,550 --> 00:29:59,110
You received a debilitating blow,
and you're drenched in your own blood...

284
00:29:59,110 --> 00:30:01,660
There's no way you can still be alive!

285
00:30:01,660 --> 00:30:06,450
I can hear... the rhythm of his steel...

286
00:30:07,330 --> 00:30:09,910
My sword is an extension of my will.

287
00:30:25,490 --> 00:30:30,310
Fine. You'll be dead for sure
after this next attack.

288
00:30:32,700 --> 00:30:33,870
All that's left...

289
00:30:34,910 --> 00:30:39,670
is to see for sure if I gained
the ability to cut steel.

290
00:30:42,300 --> 00:30:45,320
So you believe one sword
can defend against this attack.

291
00:30:47,510 --> 00:30:51,120
Don't worry. I won't defend again.

292
00:30:51,880 --> 00:30:54,460
So you've accepted
your fate. Fine by me!

293
00:30:57,610 --> 00:31:00,380
One-Sword Style Draw...

294
00:31:00,380 --> 00:31:02,170
Lion Song!

295
00:31:02,600 --> 00:31:04,180
Atomic Spurt!

296
00:31:24,880 --> 00:31:26,110
I give you my thanks.

297
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:30,770
I can get stronger still!

298
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:42,090
He really did... get stronger...
during this fight...

299
00:31:46,290 --> 00:31:47,600
What's next...?

300
00:31:49,660 --> 00:31:52,680
Are you going to cut diamond...?

301
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:56,810
That would be a waste.

302
00:31:59,440 --> 00:32:01,250
You win...

